Suspended National Police Commissioner Riah Phiyega has been deemed unfit to hold office and to be dismissed. With this Phiyega will become the third successive national police commissioner, after Bheki Cele and Jackie Selebi before her, to leave under a cloud of suspicion. She will also be the first officer to be held to account for the Marikana massacre of 2012 at Lonmin mine.Three sources have found that Phiyega lied to the Marikana Commission of Inquiry.Findings show that she failed to disclose that there were two crime scenes at which 34 mine workers were gunned down in August 2012. Scene 1, at which some of the mine workers were killed; and the infamous Scene 2, where police pursued and shot fleeing mine workers, many of whom were killed while hiding behind rocks.Full article at the source.Source: News24